108.2	Professional	Professional	A professional is a person who is paid to undertake a specialised set of tasks and to complete them for a fee. The traditional professions were doctors, lawyers, clergymen and commissioned military officers. Today, the term is applied to , architects, accountants, educators, engineers, scientists, social workers and many more. The term is also used in sports to differentiate amateur players from those who are paidâ€”hence "professional footballer" and "professional golfer".	
